    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix asymmetric comparison in x2ap_get_eNB red-black tree lookup\n\n### Summary\nThe x2ap_get_eNB function was returning incorrect results when searching for eNB entries in the red-black tree due to an asymmetric comparison function. The bug manifested when trying to look up entries by connection ID (cnx_id) in scenarios where the tree contained mixed entries identified by association ID (assoc_id) and connection ID.\n\nThe issue was in the x2ap_eNB_compare_assoc_id function which only checked p1->assoc_id to determine comparison logic but ignored p2->assoc_id, leading to inconsistent tree ordering and failed lookups.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/X2AP/x2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: Fixed comparison function to properly handle all combinations of assoc_id/cnx_id lookups\n- Made the comparison symmetric by checking both p1 and p2 assoc_id values\n- Added proper handling for mixed tree entries (some identified by assoc_id, others by cnx_id)\n\n"
}